name: Muwaffaq Imam
headline: Upgrade your coaching business with AI Agents.  | PhD candidate doing research on AI and Education
creator: True
current_position: Program Manager of Software Engineering Department
bio:
Dear Coaches and Professors are you ready to unlock the power of AI in your teaching?

I'm is a PhD student and senior instructor at Innopolis University, specializing in software engineering and generative AI.

I has been teaching for five years, instructing more than 1,500 students, and leading courses with over 300 students and seven teaching assistants. 

I'm also develops online courses on AI, programming, and software engineering, reaching thousands of students on platforms like YouTube, LinkedIn, and Udemy.

‚ûù Currently I run Coaching with AI Program 

‚ñ™Ô∏è The AI Coaching Programme is designed to help coaches, consultants, professors, and educators integrate AI into their businesses and teaching practices. You will learn how to:

‚úîÔ∏è Use AI as teaching assistants to supplement your practice with additional materials
‚úîÔ∏è Create context-aware exams and assignments 
‚úîÔ∏è Write effective prompts for optimal results 
‚úîÔ∏è Generate high-quality images for your coaching business
‚úîÔ∏è Analyse student documents and find answers efficiently
‚úîÔ∏è Generate summaries of long books or research papers 
‚úîÔ∏è Use AI tools to simplify your teaching and easily grade student work
‚úîÔ∏è Create AI agents to reflect your business and act as teaching assistants

‚ñ™Ô∏èBy joining the AI Coaching Programme, you'll stay ahead of the curve and learn how to harness the power of AI to enhance your coaching, teaching, and business.

The programme provides you with cutting-edge tools and techniques to create a modern coaching experience for your students. Muwaffaq has developed this programme based on his years of experience teaching and developing AI-powered tools and shares this knowledge with you. 

Don‚Äôt miss out‚Äîmessage me now to get started!

I am passionate about applying my analytical and technical skills to solve complex and impactful problems in machine learning and data analysis.

headline: Chief robotics scientist at Isento GmbH | AI Msc. candidate at university of Essex | inventor | researcher
creator: True

bio:
Robotics Scientist | Multi-Disciplinary Engineer

I'm the Chief Robotics Scientist at Isento GmbH in Germany, leading the development of 'pib,' an open-source 3D-printed humanoid robot.

Background:

- 5 years of High level research experience
- AI Master's at University of Essex
- Bachelors of Mechatronics Engineering at AAST
- Executive Management at University of Utah

Expertise:

- Managment, project planning and consulting
- Robotics: Mechanism design and actuation, Path planning, Reinforcement learning and control
- Mechanical Engineering: CAD, 3D printing, manufacturing, prototyping
- Electronics Engineering: Electronics, power distribution, embedded systems and actuators
- Software Engineering: Microprocessor programming (Nvidia Jetson, Raspberry Pi), ROS2 and machine learning

name: Ahmed Elkashef
headline: Senior Manager - IT Transformation Management @ Fresenius Kabi
creator: True
bio:
As a Senior Manager in IT Transformation and Operations, I bring a proven track record of leading large-scale digital initiatives and process optimization projects within complex, multinational environments. My experience spans the pharmaceutical, healthcare and automotive sectors, where I have successfully aligned IT strategies with business goals to drive organizational growth and resilience.

Currently, at Fresenius Kabi, I oversee transformative projects that harmonize IT processes, standardize operations, and foster collaborative ways of working across global teams. My role as a change agent and facilitator enables me to bring together cross-functional stakeholders to achieve shared objectives and optimize our IT service framework.

Previously, at CARIAD Estonia (Volkswagen Group), I scaled IT operations from a small team to a robust, 24/7 support structure, positioning CARIAD as a trusted IT service provider. By establishing ITIL-based processes and rigorous SLAs, I helped improve service reliability and operational efficiency, ensuring strategic alignment with business needs.

My expertise includes:
	‚Ä¢	IT Transformation and Strategic Project Leadership
	‚Ä¢	Service Management and Process Optimization
	‚Ä¢	Cross-Functional Collaboration and Stakeholder Engagement
	‚Ä¢	Team Building and Leadership in Matrix Organizations

Passionate about digital transformation, I continuously seek to implement best practices and leverage industry trends to drive value. I am always open to connecting with fellow professionals to share insights and explore opportunities for collaboration.

name: Artem Kondiukov
headline: Data Scientist in Booking.com
creator: False
bio:
I graduated from Novosibirsk State University with a major in Biology. During my studies, I have participated in different research projects, including sequencing data analysis, viral phylogeny, and neurological disorders. My thesis was dedicated to locomotor abnormalities in mice with knockout of the Kaiso gene.
Further, I moved to Innopolis to study computer science and machine learning. I worked with a team developing ML systems for analyzing chest X-ray images in terms of pathologies and anomalies. I have conducted research on neural network architectures and post-processing techniques to obtain the most accurate results.
As a data scientist at BIOCAD, I have been developing different ML-based applications aiding in early drug discovery. I dived in the industry and was able to propose and implement changes in the processes, which resulted in enhanced transparency across the computational part of the process.
Successfully completing projects and a paradigm shift in BIOCAD resulted in my promotion to head of the division and, further, to head of the department. I have been managing several cross-functional teams developing novel small molecule drugs. We built a purely Agile, startup-like environment and developed a novel anti-cancer treatment.
At the department, we also developed new technologies that could reduce risks in drug discovery or decrease the required time, including an expression platform for protein complexes, 3D cell line imaging to better predict in vivo activity and toxicity, and a computational platform supporting all stages of the drug discovery process.
After building a startup-like environment within a large company, my focus changed to working in startups in the early stages. I am interested in building disruptive products using my deep experience in biotechnology and artificial intelligence.

name: Mohammad Reza Bahrami
headline: Associate   professor | Mechanical eng. | Mathematical Modeling | Dynamical behaviour | vibration | High speed-AFM |
creator: False
past_company_2: Peter the Great St.Petersburg Polytechnic University
school_1: Peter the Great St.Petersburg Polytechnic University
bio:
- I hold a Ph.D. (2016: in Mechanical Engineering) from Peter the Great St. Petersburg Polytechnic University, St. Petersburg, Russian Federation.

- Between 2016 and 2018, I have been teaching in both English and Russian at Peter the Great St. Petersburg Polytechnic University, St. Petersburg, Russian Federation.

- In 2018, I joined Innopolis University as an Assistant Professor.

- I have more than seven years of working experience in the industry. My research focuses on creating mathematical models of dynamical systems, which are used to studying dynamical behaviors in different fields of mechanical engineering (e.g., robotics, energy, NEMS, etc.).

- I began my research work in 2010 while doing my master's degree working on the simulation and modeling of a high-speed atomic force microscope (AFM). Later, during my Ph.D. studies, I started working on designing a novel robot for inspection of the electrical transmission power lines. Currently, I am continuing my research on mathematical modeling of physical systems (robot inspector for electrical transmission lines and AFM) focusing on dynamic analysis, vibration, and designing.

- During my academic career, I successfully supervised 10+ graduate and undergraduate thesis in the mechanical engineering and computer science track, published: 2 books, 11 book chapters (in Springer), 13 journal papers (in venues like Springer Nature), 32 conference papers (full papers in venues like IFToMM).

- Across my career, I have received 1,870,000 rubles (approximately 32,542 USD) in awards, prizes, and research funding (grants). Also, I have 10+ years of experience in the industry.

Please, check my personal website to learn more about me: https://sites.google.com/view/mohammadrezabahrami/home
